Our West Coast adventure is coming to an end tomorrow. 
.
These past 16 days away from home have definitely pushed me outside my comfort zone. It almost feels like I hit the pause button of my life in Miami for a bit and went to explore.
.
Traveling can bring the best and worst out of people, I guess because of how uncomfortable it can be at times. 
.
Not knowing your way around, different cities, different people.. although within the same country, life is so different on the other side of the coast.
.
So, what do I take back home?
-Many beautiful views that the camera on my phone don’t do them justice. 
-So many lessons learned along the way.
-Priceless moments shared with others and also enjoyed on my own.
.
We went to 3 states and visited way too many cities for me to write here. 
.
Now it’s time to go home 🏡. 
.
Miami here we come ❤️✈️
.
📸 @cognitivevisions 
.

Pablo & I 💙 

Our love transforms and continues to evolve 🦋. I would be lying if I said it was still the same. Because a lot changes in 7 years.

Sometimes I look back when we started dating and all the things we’ve been through. Not all bright, not all too bad. Yet still, here we are. Standing together side by side ❤️.

When relationships are new, we tend to express the love we have for each other more often.. I remember I used to write love posts to Pablo all the time and although I haven’t really done that in a hot minute, my love for him is still intact. 

I really think our love is one of those that will always be, no matter where life takes us.

I hope everyone gets to experience a love like the one we have.. at least once in a lifetime
💙
@murdoc305 
💙

📸 @artmiamifitness 

#acrolove #parejasgoals #relationshipsbelike #loveisreal

With time and discipline anything is possible. Safety first.  I’ve been walking Slackline for about 10 years doing AcroYoga yoga and calisthenics. I definitely would say it’s been a journey of passion and love for what I do.  I don’t do this for any recognition. I do this because it’s what I love to do.  To motivate others that it’s never too late to start  When I go to an outdoor gym, I just think about doing things that are different and adrenaline rush.  it’s been in me since I was a kid and it will never change. It’s passion in love and discipline.  Along the way I hope I inspired you especially if you took the time to read this. All love ❤️
 Pablo Milian
